# Verifiable Skills Integration Walkthrough

I have successfully implemented the **GitHub and LeetCode Integration** feature from our newly proposed Placement Intelligence plan! 🚀

## What Was Changed

1. **Backend Model & API:** 
   - Expanded the [Student.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/models/Student.js) Mongoose schema to include `githubUsername`, `leetcodeUrl`, and `leetcodeUsername`.
   - Updated the profile modification route ([student-features.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/routes/student-features.js)) to parse and persist these new fields natively.

2. **AI Skill Gap Service ([skillGapAnalysis.service.js](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js)):** 
   - Introduced a new backend utility [fetchExternalStats](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js#93-125) that dynamically requests your real-time developer metrics via the official GitHub API and LeetCode Stats API.
   - Refactored the [prepareAnalysisPrompt](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/server/services/skillGapAnalysis.service.js#126-231) function to feed the verified stats (e.g., number of public repositories, followers, easy/medium/hard questions solved) directly into the AI context prompt.
   - The AI will now consider this verifiable proof-of-work when assigning proficiencies and generating your Placement Readiness insights!

3. **Frontend UI ([ProfileEditModal.jsx](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/components/student/ProfileEditModal.jsx)):** 
   - Restructured the **Links** tab within the [ProfileEditModal](file:///d:/project/Skill_Gap%20Analyser%20and%20placement%20intelligence/client/src/components/student/ProfileEditModal.jsx#70-547) component.
   - Added clean, validated input fields for GitHub and LeetCode usernames.

## How to Test it

Since your development servers are already running, you can test this instantly:

1. **Open the Student Dashboard.**
2. **Edit Profile:** Click on the "Edit Profile" button.
3. **Add Accounts:** Navigate to the **Links** tab on the left sidebar. Enter your actual GitHub and/or LeetCode usernames and click "Save Changes".
4. **Run Analysis:** Click the **Start Analysis Now** button (or trigger a re-analysis).
5. **Verify:** The AI generation will fetch your live data under the hood and utilize it to assess your skill gaps! 

> [!TIP]
> Make sure to type your exact username for accuracy. For instance, testing with a highly active LeetCode username will yield a strictly stronger Readiness Score in the AI algorithm than testing with an empty profile. 

